{
  "page": "Kings on the Three Sisters",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The title of this article is conjecture and may be subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Kings on the Three Sisters</b> were monarchs who once ruled the <a href=\"/index.php/Three_Sisters\" title=\"Three Sisters\">Three Sisters</a>, an archipelago located in the <a href=\"/index.php/Bite\" title=\"Bite\">Bite</a>, before the <a href=\"/index.php/Sistermen\" title=\"Sistermen\">Sistermen</a> came under the dominion of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kings_of_Mountain_and_Vale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings of Mountain and Vale\">Kings of Mountain and Vale</a>. Formal titles of the kings have not been revealed by <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Pirate_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Pirate Kings</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#War_Across_the_Water\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">War Across the Water</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Sistermen.27s_Rebellion\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sistermen's Rebellion</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Known_Monarchs\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known Monarchs</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kings_on_the_Three_Sisters&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Pirate_Kings\">Pirate Kings</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kings_on_the_Three_Sisters&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Pirate Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Prior to the <a href=\"/index.php/Coming_of_the_Andals\" title=\"Coming of the Andals\">coming of the Andals</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Sistermen\" title=\"Sistermen\">Sistermen</a> were an independent people with their own religion, worshipping deities known as the <a href=\"/index.php/Lady_of_the_Waves\" title=\"Lady of the Waves\">Lady of the Waves</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Skies\" title=\"Lord of the Skies\">Lord of the Skies</a>. Their monarchs acted as <a href=\"/index.php/Pirate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pirate\">pirate</a> kings<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> whose longships raided the <a href=\"/index.php/Bite\" title=\"Bite\">Bite</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Shivering_Sea\" title=\"Shivering Sea\">Shivering Sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/House_Borrell\" title=\"House Borrell\">Borrells</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Sisterton\" title=\"Sisterton\">Sisterton</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Sweetsister\" title=\"Sweetsister\">Sweetsister</a> were among the petty kings of the Sistermen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"War_Across_the_Water\">War Across the Water</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kings_on_the_Three_Sisters&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: War Across the Water\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Desiring to control the Bite, the <a href=\"/index.php/Kings_of_Winter\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings of Winter\">Kings of Winter</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">House Stark</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> eventually retaliated against the pirate kings of the Three Sisters.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> According to <a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\">maesters</a>, two thousand years ago the islands were conquered by the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> in an invasion known as the <a href=\"/index.php/Rape_of_the_Three_Sisters\" title=\"Rape of the Three Sisters\">Rape of the Three Sisters</a>. In response, the Sistermen bent the knee to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Arryn\" title=\"House Arryn\">House Arryn</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a> to expel the <a href=\"/index.php/Northmen\" title=\"Northmen\">northmen</a>, ending the era of kings on the Sisters and putting the archipelago under the rule of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kings_of_Mountain_and_Vale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings of Mountain and Vale\">Kings of Mountain and Vale</a>. Conflict over the isles between northmen and <a href=\"/index.php/Valemen\" title=\"Valemen\">Valemen</a> would continue for a thousand years in the <a href=\"/index.php/War_Across_the_Water\" title=\"War Across the Water\">War Across the Water</a>, with the Arryns eventually achieving nominal control over the Sisters.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Sistermen's_Rebellion\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sistermen.27s_Rebellion\">Sistermen's Rebellion</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kings_on_the_Three_Sisters&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Sistermen&#039;s Rebellion\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Wars_of_Conquest\" title=\"Wars of Conquest\">Wars of Conquest</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>, the Sistermen rebelled against House Arryn, declaring <a href=\"/index.php/Marla_Sunderland\" title=\"Marla Sunderland\">Marla Sunderland</a> as their queen instead of submitting to <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a>. Marla was deposed, however, when a <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavosi</a> fleet hired by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Torrhen_Stark\" title=\"Torrhen Stark\">Torrhen Stark</a>, newly-named <a href=\"/index.php/Warden_of_the_North\" title=\"Warden of the North\">Warden of the North</a>, approached the islands. Marla's brother bent the knee, ending the <a href=\"/index.php/Sistermen%27s_Rebellion\" title=\"Sistermen&#39;s Rebellion\">Sistermen's Rebellion</a>, and Marla ended her days as a <a href=\"/index.php/Silent_sister\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Silent sister\">silent sister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Monarchs\">Known Monarchs</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kings_on_the_Three_Sisters&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Monarchs\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Marla_Sunderland\" title=\"Marla Sunderland\">Marla</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Sunderland\" title=\"House Sunderland\">House Sunderland</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kings_on_the_Three_Sisters&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>For thousands of years, these islands had boasted their own cruel kings, <a href=\"/index.php/Pirates\" title=\"Pirates\">pirates</a> and raiders whose longships sailed the <a href=\"/index.php/Bite\" title=\"Bite\">Bite</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>, and even the <a href=\"/index.php/Shivering_Sea\" title=\"Shivering Sea\">Shivering Sea</a> with impunity, plundering and reaving as they would and returning to <a href=\"/index.php/Three_Sisters\" title=\"Three Sisters\">the Sisters</a> laden with <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Slaves\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slaves\">slaves</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Godric_Borrell\" title=\"Godric Borrell\">Godric's</a> forebears had been <a href=\"/index.php/Pirate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pirate\">pirate</a> kings until the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">Starks</a> came down on them with <a href=\"/index.php/Rape_of_the_Three_Sisters\" title=\"Rape of the Three Sisters\">fire and sword</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\">maesters</a> say the <a href=\"/index.php/Rape_of_the_Three_Sisters\" title=\"Rape of the Three Sisters\">Rape of the Three Sisters</a> was two thousand years ago, but <a href=\"/index.php/Sisterton\" title=\"Sisterton\">Sisterton</a> has not forgotten. <a href=\"/index.php/Sistermen\" title=\"Sistermen\">We were a free people</a> before that, with our kings ruling over us. Afterward, we had to bend our knees to the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a> to get the <a href=\"/index.php/Northmen\" title=\"Northmen\">northmen</a> out.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Godric_Borrell\" title=\"Godric Borrell\">Godric Borrell</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kings_on_the_Three_Sisters&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_9\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 9\">Chapter 9</a>, Davos I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\">2.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Vale.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0;;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:2px;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;backgr